Some ANC leaders are arrogant. They’ve forgotten that we vote for the organisation and not individuals. If you listen to the likes of Tony Yengeni, Supra Mahumapelo and Ace Magashule, you feel like giving up on this movement that we love so much. Leaders come and go, but not these arrogant comrades. They behave as if they’re the owners of the ANC. Do they expect us to respect them if one of them becomes president one day? Letter by Steve Mokwena, Soshanguve